1
00:00:08,043 --> 00:00:09,920
‐ Don't you remember
your contract?

2
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:11,421
If you break it,
your entire tribe

3
00:00:11,421 --> 00:00:15,050
will have to pay the price.

4
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:17,886
‐ After I destroy the ship,

5
00:00:17,886 --> 00:00:20,889
you promise I don't have to do
anything else, right?

6
00:00:20,889 --> 00:00:22,265
‐ Active warp, now!

7
00:00:25,894 --> 00:00:26,936
‐ No, wait!

8
00:00:28,563 --> 00:00:31,107
‐ [growls]

9
00:00:31,107 --> 00:00:33,610
‐ I can't.
I completely abandoned him.

10
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:38,239
I just left him for dead
back there.

11
00:00:38,239 --> 00:00:40,408
I guess I'm not much
of a solider, am I?

12
00:00:40,408 --> 00:00:42,285
NILVAL: We shall cease
all protective operations

13
00:00:42,285 --> 00:00:44,245
of this dying planet.

14
00:00:44,245 --> 00:00:48,458
From this point on,
this fleet has a new mission.

15
00:00:48,458 --> 00:00:51,920
We will dedicate
our meager resources to you.

16
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:56,049
‐ The path, I will find it.

17
00:00:56,049 --> 00:00:59,427
I promise.
Hold on.

18
00:00:59,427 --> 00:01:02,430
["Gravitation" by Angela]

19
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:05,517
[woman singing in Japanese]

20
00:01:05,517 --> 00:01:12,524
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21
00:02:33,021 --> 00:02:36,024
[rumbling]

22
00:02:49,162 --> 00:02:51,748
NILVAL: Status update.
LIEUTENANT: Yes, ma'am.

23
00:02:51,748 --> 00:02:54,417
Our strategic positioning
is 80% complete.

24
00:02:54,417 --> 00:02:58,088
There has been a slight delay
in the relocation of the core.

25
00:02:58,088 --> 00:02:59,589
‐ Well, we don't have much time.

26
00:02:59,589 --> 00:03:00,590
The battle is about to begin.

27
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:01,716
LIEUTENANT: Yes, ma'am.

28
00:03:01,716 --> 00:03:03,134
<i>[soft music]</i>

29
00:03:03,134 --> 00:03:05,303
[booming]

30
00:03:07,222 --> 00:03:13,061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31
00:03:13,061 --> 00:03:15,563
PHAETH O: More Iron Tribe.

32
00:03:15,563 --> 00:03:18,942
Are they trying to help
that ship escape?

33
00:03:18,942 --> 00:03:25,657
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34
00:03:25,657 --> 00:03:27,242
‐ We have found them.

35
00:03:27,242 --> 00:03:30,370
Because of your failure, there
are more ships to destroy,

36
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:31,496
Mehitak.

37
00:03:34,374 --> 00:03:37,502
Now go.
Refusal is not an option.

38
00:03:52,225 --> 00:03:53,935
MAN: A full Hedron has been
detected.

39
00:03:53,935 --> 00:03:55,395
It's the Silver Tribe.

40
00:03:55,395 --> 00:03:57,021
NILVAL: Pearl Core,
maintain current position.

41
00:03:57,021 --> 00:04:00,108
Ruby Core and Topaz Core,
complete formation.

42
00:04:00,108 --> 00:04:03,570
All strategic fleet positioning
will be relative to Blue Core.

43
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:06,614
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

44
00:04:06,614 --> 00:04:13,621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45
00:04:20,461 --> 00:04:23,631
‐ Ruby Core at minus 240‐13.

46
00:04:23,631 --> 00:04:27,177
Topaz Core at 13‐11‐54.

47
00:04:27,177 --> 00:04:28,803
LIEUTENANT: Prepare to attack.

48
00:04:28,803 --> 00:04:31,723
WOMAN: Ready, sir!

49
00:04:31,723 --> 00:04:32,724
‐ Fire.

50
00:04:32,724 --> 00:04:35,226
[warbling]

51
00:04:38,229 --> 00:04:39,522
[boom]

52
00:04:41,482 --> 00:04:48,489
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53
00:04:48,489 --> 00:04:50,491
[rumbling]

54
00:04:50,491 --> 00:04:55,330
<i>[tense music]</i>

55
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:57,832
WOMAN: Massive spatiotemporal
shock detected.

56
00:04:57,832 --> 00:04:59,667
MAN: Their gravity signature
is growing.

57
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,336
More vessels are coming out
of warp!

58
00:05:01,336 --> 00:05:03,546
‐ How long can her fleet
possibly hold back

59
00:05:03,546 --> 00:05:06,758
such an overwhelming enemy?

60
00:05:06,758 --> 00:05:10,178
Please, Nilval, don't die.

61
00:05:10,178 --> 00:05:17,352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

62
00:05:17,352 --> 00:05:20,021
‐ Receiving data
via the cycle line.

63
00:05:20,021 --> 00:05:21,814
‐ Coordinates from the princess.

64
00:05:21,814 --> 00:05:24,609
Have navigation analyze them
and calculate our route

65
00:05:24,609 --> 00:05:25,944
immediately.

66
00:05:27,612 --> 00:05:30,365
[booming]

67
00:05:39,332 --> 00:05:42,877
[flames crackling]

68
00:05:42,877 --> 00:05:44,754
YUTY: Karkinos.

69
00:05:44,754 --> 00:05:47,131
What is it?
What's happening?

70
00:05:49,217 --> 00:05:52,887
Impossible.
He can't defeat you.

71
00:05:57,141 --> 00:06:00,144
PROME O: Yuty's confidence has
begun to dissolve.

72
00:06:00,144 --> 00:06:02,272
LECTY: If Karkinos continues
to fight,

73
00:06:02,272 --> 00:06:03,898
he will perish.

74
00:06:03,898 --> 00:06:07,819
I assume that is one of
the Labors in his contract.

75
00:06:07,819 --> 00:06:10,488
‐ I do wonder what Mehitak
is doing.

76
00:06:10,488 --> 00:06:12,073
‐ Mehitak is weeping.

77
00:06:12,073 --> 00:06:16,661
If it were possible, I would
step in and take his place.

78
00:06:16,661 --> 00:06:18,997
‐ His fate is his own burden.

79
00:06:18,997 --> 00:06:22,792
You see, that is the nature
of contracts such as ours.

80
00:06:22,792 --> 00:06:26,296
No one may shoulder the burden
of someone else's destiny.

81
00:06:26,296 --> 00:06:28,256
In that respect, we are alone.

82
00:06:28,256 --> 00:06:31,551
‐ Yes, but why?
It's so cruel.

83
00:06:31,551 --> 00:06:34,762
The pain:
it makes no sense to me.

84
00:06:34,762 --> 00:06:37,640
What is the true purpose
of these Labors?

85
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:40,226
[booming]

86
00:06:40,226 --> 00:06:42,353
What good do the Golden Tribe
foresee

87
00:06:42,353 --> 00:06:44,063
when they bound us
to this contract

88
00:06:44,063 --> 00:06:47,942
and made us pawns in a bloody
war to control the universe?

89
00:06:47,942 --> 00:06:50,737
YUTY: Karkinos!

90
00:06:50,737 --> 00:06:53,448
You fool.
Kill him now.

91
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,122
NILVAL: Where are they now?

92
00:07:01,122 --> 00:07:03,624
LIEUTENANT: The "Argonaut"
is .02 AUs behind us

93
00:07:03,624 --> 00:07:05,752
and moving at full speed.

94
00:07:05,752 --> 00:07:09,005
‐ But why are they moving at
full speed off of a Starway?

95
00:07:09,005 --> 00:07:10,465
Mm.
What do you want to bet

96
00:07:10,465 --> 00:07:12,467
Princess Dhianeila's
showing them the way?

97
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:13,426
[beeping]

98
00:07:13,426 --> 00:07:15,553
‐ Unidentified vessel detected.

99
00:07:15,553 --> 00:07:17,764
Estimated arrival in 20 seconds.

100
00:07:17,764 --> 00:07:19,223
‐ Send orders to Pearl Core.

101
00:07:19,223 --> 00:07:21,809
Deploy generators
and battlefield alignment.

102
00:07:21,809 --> 00:07:24,854
[warbling]

103
00:07:27,231 --> 00:07:29,901
[whooshing]

104
00:08:00,348 --> 00:08:01,766
[whooshing]

105
00:08:01,766 --> 00:08:03,142
NILVAL: Status report.

106
00:08:03,142 --> 00:08:04,644
LIEUTENANT: No progress
on the front line.

107
00:08:04,644 --> 00:08:08,397
The enemy force continues
to grow in numbers.

108
00:08:08,397 --> 00:08:11,442
[whooshing]

109
00:08:14,612 --> 00:08:17,865
WOMAN: Unknown vessel detected
in Ruby Core's firing line.

110
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:20,034
It looks like it could be
a Nodos.

111
00:08:20,034 --> 00:08:21,786
‐ Let me see it on the display.

112
00:08:21,786 --> 00:08:22,870
WOMAN: Yes, ma'am!

113
00:08:24,789 --> 00:08:26,332
LIEUTENANT: It is a Nodos.

114
00:08:26,332 --> 00:08:27,875
MAN: The Pearl Core is not going
to make it.

115
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:29,669
‐ Order the Dralion unit in

116
00:08:29,669 --> 00:08:31,379
to compensate
for the defense gap.

117
00:08:31,379 --> 00:08:34,423
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

118
00:08:34,423 --> 00:08:41,472
<i>♪ ♪</i>

119
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,475
[blasters firing]

120
00:08:47,061 --> 00:08:50,064
MAN: The enemy appears
unaffected by our attacks!

121
00:08:50,064 --> 00:08:52,567
‐ I don't understand
what it's doing.

122
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:55,611
[blasters firing]

123
00:08:58,906 --> 00:09:01,909
The beast seems invincible.
Why isn't it attacking?

124
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:05,121
‐ Does it expect some favor
in return?

125
00:09:06,414 --> 00:09:07,790
Show it no mercy.

126
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:10,460
Pearl Core generator
at maximum capacity!

127
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,420
Synchronize with the
planetary magnetic field

128
00:09:12,420 --> 00:09:16,299
and create a gravitational
force to pin that monster down!

129
00:09:16,299 --> 00:09:23,347
<i>♪ ♪</i>

130
00:09:30,813 --> 00:09:33,024
The Nodos might be able to dodge
one of the beams,

131
00:09:33,024 --> 00:09:35,526
but there's no way it'll be able
to dodge them all.

132
00:09:35,526 --> 00:09:37,195
Draw the net in!

133
00:09:37,195 --> 00:09:38,488
WOMAN: Yes, ma'am!

134
00:09:41,824 --> 00:09:42,992
[blasters firing]

135
00:09:42,992 --> 00:09:45,953
[warbling]

136
00:09:45,953 --> 00:09:47,371
MAN: Grab sync complete.

137
00:09:47,371 --> 00:09:48,789
‐ All ships open fire.

138
00:09:48,789 --> 00:09:55,796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

139
00:09:58,174 --> 00:10:00,468
WOMAN: Captain, we've picked up
multiple anthills,

140
00:10:00,468 --> 00:10:01,761
approaching fast!

141
00:10:01,761 --> 00:10:04,222
‐ They must be a group that got
separated.

142
00:10:04,222 --> 00:10:06,557
Maintain heading.
Prepare to engage.

143
00:10:06,557 --> 00:10:08,476
‐ Energy fluctuations ahead,
sir.

144
00:10:08,476 --> 00:10:10,478
Seems the ant heaps
are moving to intercept us

145
00:10:10,478 --> 00:10:12,980
before we get to the source
of the pulses.

146
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:15,316
‐ Is that Age?

147
00:10:15,316 --> 00:10:17,610
If it is him, then the poor
boy's been fighting

148
00:10:17,610 --> 00:10:20,238
for more than 200 hours
straight.

149
00:10:23,824 --> 00:10:25,117
‐ Hold on, Age.

150
00:10:29,497 --> 00:10:30,998
‐ [growling]

151
00:10:30,998 --> 00:10:31,999
[boom]

152
00:10:33,417 --> 00:10:35,127
[booming]

153
00:10:47,515 --> 00:10:48,849
[crackling]

154
00:10:58,192 --> 00:11:00,027
[whooshing]

155
00:11:02,113 --> 00:11:03,197
[growls]

156
00:11:07,201 --> 00:11:08,619
[booming]

157
00:11:11,581 --> 00:11:13,624
[wind blowing]

158
00:11:16,043 --> 00:11:18,129
‐ [panting]

159
00:11:42,069 --> 00:11:45,156
‐ [panting softly]

160
00:12:00,504 --> 00:12:02,256
‐ [sighs]

161
00:12:02,256 --> 00:12:04,216
Here I come!

162
00:12:04,216 --> 00:12:06,093
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

163
00:12:06,093 --> 00:12:08,929
‐ You barbarian.

164
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:15,936
<i>♪ ♪</i>

165
00:12:18,939 --> 00:12:20,358
‐ Karkinos?

166
00:12:20,358 --> 00:12:21,984
Stop toying with him.

167
00:12:21,984 --> 00:12:23,944
I know you can do better
than that.

168
00:12:23,944 --> 00:12:30,743
<i>♪ ♪</i>

169
00:12:30,743 --> 00:12:34,747
‐ The ship we're searching for
isn't here.

170
00:12:34,747 --> 00:12:36,791
Where could it be?

171
00:12:36,791 --> 00:12:39,251
[whirring]

172
00:12:53,307 --> 00:12:54,809
‐ High energy field
concentrating

173
00:12:54,809 --> 00:12:56,477
around the Nodos.

174
00:12:56,477 --> 00:12:58,771
‐ I've got a feeling
it's on the offensive now.

175
00:12:58,771 --> 00:13:00,815
‐ So the monster finally stirs.

176
00:13:00,815 --> 00:13:02,316
All ships disperse.

177
00:13:02,316 --> 00:13:04,318
I want the medic and supply
ships to remain close

178
00:13:04,318 --> 00:13:06,028
to Pearl Core.

179
00:13:06,028 --> 00:13:08,531
Blue Core, release your entire
reserve of blooms immediately.

180
00:13:08,531 --> 00:13:10,324
Crush every last ant!

181
00:13:10,324 --> 00:13:17,373
<i>♪ ♪</i>

182
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:21,460
‐ [moaning]

183
00:13:24,839 --> 00:13:27,174
‐ I want 80% firepower
on the Nodos.

184
00:13:27,174 --> 00:13:28,592
Focus the rest on the ants.

185
00:13:28,592 --> 00:13:30,511
‐ Hold on.
No, it can't be.

186
00:13:30,511 --> 00:13:34,223
Its energy levels exceeds
shield limits.

187
00:13:34,223 --> 00:13:35,516
‐ Begin targeting now.

188
00:13:35,516 --> 00:13:37,560
WOMAN: Target acquired!

189
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:44,608
<i>♪ ♪</i>

190
00:13:46,110 --> 00:13:47,653
[electricity crackling]

191
00:13:50,823 --> 00:13:52,533
‐ Target lock complete.

192
00:13:52,533 --> 00:13:55,327
‐ Margin of error is now .01%.

193
00:13:55,327 --> 00:13:56,787
‐ Fire!

194
00:13:56,787 --> 00:13:59,832
[blasters fire]

195
00:14:09,884 --> 00:14:12,887
[cracking]

196
00:14:12,887 --> 00:14:14,930
[intense rumbling]

197
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:15,931
[booming]

198
00:14:15,931 --> 00:14:16,974
[both gasp]

199
00:14:16,974 --> 00:14:18,017
Pull up, now!

200
00:14:19,894 --> 00:14:21,020
‐ [gasps]

201
00:14:23,022 --> 00:14:25,107
Oh, no.

202
00:14:25,107 --> 00:14:27,151
‐ [growling]

203
00:14:30,112 --> 00:14:31,906
[rumbling]

204
00:14:31,906 --> 00:14:38,913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

205
00:15:07,775 --> 00:15:09,818
‐ [roaring]

206
00:15:11,987 --> 00:15:14,865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

207
00:15:14,865 --> 00:15:17,117
‐ Now what?
I want a full report.

208
00:15:17,117 --> 00:15:19,119
‐ We detected a catastrophic
burst of energy

209
00:15:19,119 --> 00:15:20,955
within the Planet Huelgoat.

210
00:15:20,955 --> 00:15:24,124
‐ I can that,
but what the hell happened?

211
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:27,086
<i>♪ ♪</i>

212
00:15:27,086 --> 00:15:29,004
‐ The planet...

213
00:15:29,004 --> 00:15:30,798
has died.

214
00:15:30,798 --> 00:15:36,804
<i>♪ ♪</i>

215
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:48,357
WOMAN: Two [inaudible]
supremely damaged!

216
00:15:48,357 --> 00:15:50,609
We lost contact with 60%
of the fleet!

217
00:15:50,609 --> 00:15:53,362
MAN: Ruby Core and Blue Core
have sustained casualties!

218
00:15:53,362 --> 00:15:55,281
‐ Regroup with
the Dralion unit.

219
00:15:55,281 --> 00:15:57,950
All ships reposition behind
the satellite fortress.

220
00:15:57,950 --> 00:15:59,577
Where's Pearl Core?

221
00:15:59,577 --> 00:16:01,537
MAN: It's still engaged
with the enemy, Nodos.

222
00:16:01,537 --> 00:16:08,669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

223
00:16:10,963 --> 00:16:14,341
‐ How long do we have before
total planetary destruction?

224
00:16:14,341 --> 00:16:15,759
‐ Three minutes at most, ma'am.

225
00:16:15,759 --> 00:16:17,761
‐ We'll maintain our hold
until then.

226
00:16:17,761 --> 00:16:20,055
All vessels including
Ruby Core and Blue Core

227
00:16:20,055 --> 00:16:22,016
move into attack positions.

228
00:16:22,016 --> 00:16:23,601
‐ Commander,
we need to disengage

229
00:16:23,601 --> 00:16:25,477
the gravitational field
and release the Nodos.

230
00:16:25,477 --> 00:16:29,982
If we take one more hit,
that'll be the end of us!

231
00:16:29,982 --> 00:16:31,900
‐ What do you suggest we do,
Lieutenant?

232
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:33,652
Leave the "Argonaut"
to the enemy?

233
00:16:33,652 --> 00:16:35,446
Did our troops all die in vain?

234
00:16:35,446 --> 00:16:38,782
Was an entire planet destroyed
for no reason?

235
00:16:49,209 --> 00:16:52,588
I'm as useless as the dead
commanders before me.

236
00:16:52,588 --> 00:16:54,798
I guess I should have known,
huh?

237
00:16:54,798 --> 00:16:57,217
This mission is suicide.

238
00:16:57,217 --> 00:16:58,969
I wouldn't blame them
for ignoring me

239
00:16:58,969 --> 00:17:00,596
and deserting this battle.

240
00:17:02,348 --> 00:17:05,017
WOMAN: Ruby Core standing by
at route N3.

241
00:17:05,017 --> 00:17:08,270
And Pearl Core currently
standing by at point NA3.

242
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,564
‐ Blue Core and all other
available battleships

243
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:12,399
are standing by at
appropriate coordinates.

244
00:17:12,399 --> 00:17:14,902
‐ All reserve ships
are currently en route

245
00:17:14,902 --> 00:17:17,780
to take up offensive positions.

246
00:17:17,780 --> 00:17:20,407
‐ Not a single person
has deserted us.

247
00:17:20,407 --> 00:17:22,117
‐ Your fleet believes in you,
Commander,

248
00:17:22,117 --> 00:17:25,079
and they will remain loyal
to you until the very end.

249
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,121
‐ Hmm.

250
00:17:27,873 --> 00:17:31,251
I don't know if that makes them
honorable or just foolish.

251
00:17:31,251 --> 00:17:36,590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

252
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,592
[growling]

253
00:17:42,388 --> 00:17:45,432
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

254
00:17:45,432 --> 00:17:53,107
<i>♪ ♪</i>

255
00:17:53,107 --> 00:17:54,149
[boom]

256
00:17:59,989 --> 00:18:02,741
[roaring]

257
00:18:05,661 --> 00:18:07,371
[cracking and hissing]

258
00:18:07,371 --> 00:18:09,790
‐ [gasps]

259
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:11,375
Karkinos.

260
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:14,420
[warbling]

261
00:18:22,428 --> 00:18:23,887
PROME O: Why?

262
00:18:23,887 --> 00:18:26,932
Why would the Golden Tribe give
such a powerful Nodos

263
00:18:26,932 --> 00:18:28,600
to the Iron Tribe?

264
00:18:32,563 --> 00:18:36,817
I often wonder if they intended
to split the universe in two.

265
00:18:38,777 --> 00:18:40,070
‐ Split in two?

266
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:47,119
<i>[soft orchestral music]</i>

267
00:18:47,119 --> 00:18:51,874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

268
00:18:51,874 --> 00:18:53,542
[revving]

269
00:18:53,542 --> 00:19:00,591
<i>♪ ♪</i>

270
00:19:02,134 --> 00:19:04,344
‐ All right, this scuffle
shouldn't be any problem.

271
00:19:04,344 --> 00:19:06,680
It seems Nilval has already
suppressed a majority

272
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,223
of the enemy fleet.

273
00:19:08,223 --> 00:19:09,433
Hmm.

274
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:11,727
WOMAN: All units return
to the ship.

275
00:19:11,727 --> 00:19:13,437
We are now making preparations

276
00:19:13,437 --> 00:19:16,315
to move out of conventional
space and into active warp.

277
00:19:16,315 --> 00:19:19,193
WOMAN: I repeat, all units
return to the ship.

278
00:19:19,193 --> 00:19:20,903
IOLAOUS:
Did we find the Starway?

279
00:19:20,903 --> 00:19:23,864
No, it must be the princess.

280
00:19:23,864 --> 00:19:31,497
<i>♪ ♪</i>

281
00:19:31,497 --> 00:19:33,582
‐ Everyone on board
the "Argonaut" is in danger

282
00:19:33,582 --> 00:19:35,250
because of me.

283
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,503
I can't help but worry.

284
00:19:37,503 --> 00:19:40,380
I'm so frightened.

285
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:46,804
‐ I'll be all right.
I promise you.

286
00:19:46,804 --> 00:19:48,889
Do you remember?
The 12 Labors.

287
00:19:48,889 --> 00:19:50,224
I'm here to protect you.

288
00:19:50,224 --> 00:19:51,725
‐ But who's going
to protect you?

289
00:19:51,725 --> 00:19:53,977
‐ Me and Bellcross will make
a path for you.

290
00:19:53,977 --> 00:19:56,939
I promise the "Argonaut"
will make it out,

291
00:19:56,939 --> 00:19:59,274
even if it means that we have
to stay behind.

292
00:19:59,274 --> 00:20:02,069
But don't be sad;
you'll see us again.

293
00:20:06,031 --> 00:20:07,658
‐ Age.

294
00:20:07,658 --> 00:20:09,201
[gasps]

295
00:20:09,201 --> 00:20:10,577
MOBEEDO:
Transmit the ship's course

296
00:20:10,577 --> 00:20:12,121
to the Azz‐Azoth fleet.

297
00:20:12,121 --> 00:20:13,705
They've completely lost
their way

298
00:20:13,705 --> 00:20:16,083
if the Planet Huelgoat
was really destroyed.

299
00:20:16,083 --> 00:20:18,043
Without that planet,
they'll never find the Starway.

300
00:20:18,043 --> 00:20:20,379
Our ship is the only chance
they've got right now.

301
00:20:20,379 --> 00:20:22,923
DHIANEILA: Captain, I sense
a hostile presence

302
00:20:22,923 --> 00:20:24,758
coming toward us.

303
00:20:24,758 --> 00:20:27,094
‐ Deploy the shield
at maximum output!

304
00:20:27,094 --> 00:20:30,597
Scan for spatiotemporal shock
in our vicinity.

305
00:20:30,597 --> 00:20:31,932
‐ Shock detected.

306
00:20:31,932 --> 00:20:33,183
It's right above us!

307
00:20:33,183 --> 00:20:34,685
‐ What?

308
00:20:34,685 --> 00:20:36,770
[gasps]

309
00:20:36,770 --> 00:20:38,355
WOMAN: Ship identified.

310
00:20:38,355 --> 00:20:40,524
Sir, that ship's a full Hedron.

311
00:20:40,524 --> 00:20:42,276
‐ It's the Silver Tribe.

312
00:20:42,276 --> 00:20:45,279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

313
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:46,405
‐ Found you.

314
00:20:46,405 --> 00:20:49,241
There's no use running.

315
00:20:49,241 --> 00:20:51,285
You won't get away.

316
00:20:51,285 --> 00:20:52,661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

317
00:20:52,661 --> 00:20:54,788
[electricity crackling]

318
00:20:57,291 --> 00:21:01,128
<i>♪ ♪</i>

319
00:21:01,128 --> 00:21:03,005
‐ There's just not enough power
to maintain

320
00:21:03,005 --> 00:21:04,715
both shields and active warp.

321
00:21:04,715 --> 00:21:08,635
MAN: Ceasing active warps and
all available power shields.

322
00:21:08,635 --> 00:21:14,433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

323
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:16,977
‐ The timing couldn't be worse
for this to happen.

324
00:21:16,977 --> 00:21:18,478
Damn your kind!

325
00:21:18,478 --> 00:21:21,815
How do I choose between
active warp and the shields?

326
00:21:21,815 --> 00:21:24,234
DHIANEILA: You must take
the path given to you.

327
00:21:24,234 --> 00:21:26,778
‐ What path, Princess?

328
00:21:26,778 --> 00:21:28,155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

329
00:21:28,155 --> 00:21:29,448
[music stops]

330
00:21:31,366 --> 00:21:33,035
‐ Stop this at once!

331
00:21:35,162 --> 00:21:38,290
‐ [gasping and groaning]

332
00:21:38,290 --> 00:21:41,335
<i>[tense music]</i>

333
00:21:41,335 --> 00:21:46,423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

334
00:21:46,423 --> 00:21:48,842
[booming]

335
00:21:48,842 --> 00:21:50,260
‐ Sir, the attack has stopped!

336
00:21:50,260 --> 00:21:51,637
‐ Disengage the shields!

337
00:21:51,637 --> 00:21:53,055
Enter active warp!

338
00:21:54,306 --> 00:21:55,515
[shimmering tone]

339
00:21:57,517 --> 00:21:58,518
‐ [sighs]

340
00:22:03,774 --> 00:22:04,858
What?

341
00:22:06,818 --> 00:22:08,195
What happened?

342
00:22:12,199 --> 00:22:13,408
[boom]

343
00:22:15,244 --> 00:22:16,954
[alarm blaring]
‐ [gasps] Oh, no!

344
00:22:16,954 --> 00:22:18,080
The princess!

345
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:19,248
‐ Are you all right?

346
00:22:19,248 --> 00:22:20,916
‐ Quick, open the pod!

347
00:22:24,211 --> 00:22:25,754
Princess Dhianeila!

348
00:22:31,635 --> 00:22:34,554
Please, talk to me!

349
00:22:34,554 --> 00:22:35,764
Dhianeila?

350
00:22:39,685 --> 00:22:42,688
["Azurite" by Tae Urakabe]

351
00:22:42,688 --> 00:22:45,774
[woman singing in Japanese]

